com.cronos.onlinereview.phases
Class SubmissionPhaseHandler

java.lang.Object
  com.cronos.onlinereview.phases.AbstractPhaseHandler
      com.cronos.onlinereview.phases.SubmissionPhaseHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.topcoder.management.phase.PhaseHandler
public class SubmissionPhaseHandler
extends AbstractPhaseHandler

This class implements PhaseHandler interface to provide methods to check if a phase can be executed and to add extra logic to execute a phase. It will be used by Phase Management component. It is configurable using an input namespace. The configurable parameters include database connection, email sending and the required number of submissions that pass screening. This class handle the submission phase. If the input is of other phase types, PhaseNotSupportedException will be thrown.

The submission phase can start as soon as the dependencies are met and start time is reached, and can stop when the following conditions met:

  • The dependencies are met
  • The phase's end time is reached.
  • If manual screening is absent, the number of submissions that have passed auto-screening meets the required number;
  • If manual screening is required, the number of submissions that have passed manual screening meets the required number.

Note that screening phase can be started during a submission phase.

There is no additional logic for executing this phase.

Thread safety: This class is thread safe because it is immutable.

Method Detail

canPerform

public boolean canPerform(com.topcoder.project.phases.Phase phase)
                   throws com.topcoder.management.phase.PhaseHandlingException
Check if the input phase can be executed or not. This method will check the phase status to see what will be executed. This method will be called by canStart() and canEnd() methods of PhaseManager implementations in Phase Management component.

If the input phase status is Scheduled, then it will check if the phase can be started using the following conditions: the dependencies are met and Its start time is reached.

If the input phase status is Open, then it will check if the phase can be stopped using the following conditions:

  • The dependencies are met
  • The phase's end time is reached.
  • If manual screening is absent, the number of submissions that have passed auto-screening meets the required number;
  • If manual screening is required, the number of submissions that have passed manual screening meets the required number.

If the input phase status is Closed, then PhaseHandlingException will be thrown.

Parameters:
phase - The input phase to check.
Returns:
True if the input phase can be executed, false otherwise.
Throws:
PhaseNotSupportedException - if the input phase type is not "Submission" type.
com.topcoder.management.phase.PhaseHandlingException - if there is any error occurred while processing the phase.
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the input is null.

perform

public void perform(com.topcoder.project.phases.Phase phase,
                    java.lang.String operator)
             throws com.topcoder.management.phase.PhaseHandlingException
Provides additional logic to execute a phase. This method will be called by start() and end() methods of PhaseManager implementations in Phase Management component. This method can send email to a group os users associated with timeline notification for the project. The email can be send on start phase or end phase base on configuration settings.

If the input phase status is Closed, then PhaseHandlingException will be thrown.

Parameters:
phase - The input phase to check.
operator - The operator that execute the phase.
Throws:
PhaseNotSupportedException - if the input phase type is not "Submission" type.
com.topcoder.management.phase.PhaseHandlingException - if there is any error occurred while processing the phase.
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the input parameters is null or empty string.
